extends layout

block content
  .container.clearfix
    #welcome.sixteen.columns
      .qoute
        .ten-and-half.columns.omega
          blockquote
            | On the&nbsp;
            a(href='http://www.angularjs.org/') AngularJS
            | &nbsp;team, we rely on testing and we always
            | seek better tools to make our life easier.
            | That's why we created<br>Karma - a test runner that fits
            | all our needs.
        .four-and-half.columns.alpha
          a.btn-github.link(href='https://github.com/karma-runner/karma')
            span
              i.icon-github-alt
              | &nbsp; View project on GitHub
          a.btn-npm.link(href='https://npmjs.org/package/karma')
            span
              i.icon-hdd
              | &nbsp; npm install -g karma

  #slider
    .container.clearfix.bottom
      .sixteen.columns
        .flex-container
          .flexslider
            ul.slides
              li
                a(href='http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MVw8N3hTfCI')
                  img(src='/assets/img/screencast.png', alt='Screencast')
                p.flex-caption
                  span Introductory Screencast
                  | The spectacular quick start to Testacular.
              li
                a(href='http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5mHjJ4xf_K0')
                  img(src='/assets/img/jseverywhere.png', alt='JS.everywhere 2012')
                p.flex-caption
                  span JS Everywhere 2012 Paris
                  | Watch Vojta JÃ­na presenting Testacular at JS.everywhere.

  .container
    .sixteen.columns.bottom
      p.bold.large.center.
        Things should be simple. We believe in testing and so we wanna make
        it as simple as possible.
    .sixteen.columns.bottom
      p.center
        :markdown
          The main goal for Karma is to bring a productive testing
          environment to developers. An environment, where they don't have
          to set up many things and rather just write the code and get an
          instant feedback. Because getting a quick feedback is what makes you
          productive and [creative](http://vimeo.com/36579366).

    .clearfix
    .our-services
      ul
        li.one-third.column
          .icon-box
            i.icon-mobile-phone.icon-2x
          h3 Test on Real Devices
          p
            | Test your code on real browsers and real devices such as phones,
            | tablets or headless PhantomJS.
        li.one-third.column
          .icon-box
            i.icon-resize-small.icon-2x
          h3 Remote Control
          p
            | Control the whole workflow from the command line or your IDE -
            | just save a file and Karma will run all the tests.
        li.one-third.column
          .icon-box
            i.icon-globe.icon-2x
          h3 Testing Framework Agnostic
          p
            :markdown
              Describe your tests with [Jasmine](http://pivotal.github.com/jasmine/),
              [Mocha](http://visionmedia.github.com/mocha/),
              [QUnit](http://qunitjs.com/). Or write a simple adapter for any framework you like.

        li.one-third.column.last
          .icon-box
            i.icon-group.icon-2x
          h3 Open Source
          p
            | Developed for and maintained by the open source community at 
            a(href='https://github.com/karma-runner/karma') GitHub
            | .
        li.one-third.column.last
          .icon-box
            i.icon-magic.icon-2x
          h3 Easy Debugging
          p
            | Easy debugging directly from your IDE (WebStorm) or Chrome.
        li.one-third.column.last
          .icon-box
            i.icon-refresh.icon-2x
          h3 Continuous Integration
          p
            :markdown
              Simple integration with [Jenkins](plus/Jenkins-CI.html),
              [Travis](plus/Travis-CI.html) or
              [Teamcity](plus/Teamcity.html).

  .container.clearfix.bottom
    .sixteen.columns.bottom
      hr
    .sixteen.columns
      p.center
        | For more motivation on why to use Karma and why we did it, check out
        | the blog post on 
        a(href='http://googletesting.blogspot.com/2012/11/testacular-spectacular-test-runner-for.html') Google Testing
        | .
